INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('767', '1', '2014-04-24 17:11:57', '2014-04-24 17:11:57', '<h1>Version 2.4 of TFS Timetracker Released Today.</h1>\r\nThank you so much for such a lot precious feedback! Here is a lot of changes you have been waiting for.\r\n<h3>The \'Timetracker Tab\' in every item</h3>\r\nWe added the tab “Timetracker” as an extension to Team Foundation Server. Whenever you open an item in Team Foundation Server web access, you have this new tab displaying an analysis of time efforts.<!--more-->\r\n<img class=\"alignright wp-image-762 size-full\" src=\"http://blog.tfs-timetracker.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/24-04-2014-19-05-19.png\" alt=\"24-04-2014 19-05-19\" width=\"556\" height=\"230\" />\r\n<h3>The \'Completed Work Autofill\'</h3>\r\nNow you can setup an automatic entering of tracked time into a selected field in the work item, e.g. completed work. If the user likes to adjust this automatic filled in value, he manually sets a variant which is always kept, directly in the field in web access. This new feature is covering the requirement in an environment with Microsoft Project Server.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-757 size-full\" src=\"http://blog.tfs-timetracker.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/24-04-2014-17-40-001.png\" alt=\"24-04-2014 17-40-00\" width=\"586\" height=\"24\" />\r\n<h3>\'My Times\' is now your personal calendar</h3>\r\nIntroducing the all new “Calendar View” as standard for My Times. See all bookings in a neat monthly calendar, with totals on weeks and months, and an integrated details list. Add times to a day just with one click.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-755 size-full\" src=\"http://blog.tfs-timetracker.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/140424screenshot.png\" alt=\"140424screenshot\" width=\"970\" height=\"263\" />\r\n<h3>\'Magic guessing\' for new trackings</h3>\r\nWe call it “the magic guessing” - the add/edit times dialog now offers a list of computed work items for that particular day, based on what was assigned to you, in process and in frequent use - the first item has a good chance to be the one to book your times on.\r\n<h3>Access your queries for selecting items in new trackings</h3>\r\nThe next help for the add/edit times dialog - a selector that presents you items to choose from based on the available queries in Team Foundation Server - personal and shared.\r\n<h3>Budgets reloaded</h3>\r\nThe view “Budgets” was redesigned, it consists now of a list on the left side and a detail view on the right. The detail view informs in addition about what is counted in the total sum, included and excluded iterations and items.\r\n<h3>Who doesn\'t like speed?</h3>\r\nWe managed to eliminate some more speed bottle necks, page loading time was greatly reduced.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', '2.4 Is Here With Seven Big News!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '740-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-04-24 17:11:57', '2014-04-24 17:11:57', '', '740', 'http://www.tfs-timetracker.com/740-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
