INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1196', '1', '2015-05-01 13:12:02', '2015-05-01 13:12:02', '<h1>Say hello to API and VS Integration!</h1>\r\nWe had quite an exiting week by finishing tests for support of Team Foundation Server  2015, some updates to our shop, and after running our beta for a couple of weeks, finally releasing the new TFS Timetracker 2.6. So it\'s here, available for download!<!--more-->\r\n\r\nWe are working down the wishlist from our customers. With top priority, there was the demand for accessing data, like from other systems in your environment, from your analytics app like Microsoft Excel or totally customized by some code.\r\n<h2>TFS Timetracker API</h2>\r\nYou can configure the API from configuration &gt; settings in the web interface. Our developement goal was to implement a solution both fast, easy and powerful, with making available as many information from within Team Foundation Server as possible. For this, we decided to add an extra table filled with enriched time records. You\'ll find this table named \"dbo.btr_Export\" in the database of the collection from Team Foundation Server, e.g. in \"Default Collection\".\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.tfs-timetracker.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/APIAvailableFields.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1192\" src=\"http://blog.tfs-timetracker.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/APIAvailableFields.png\" alt=\"APIAvailableFields\" width=\"930\" height=\"222\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe columns of this table are fully customizable, 28 columns from Team Foundation Server standard core information, 25 columns from TFS Timetracker as well as 5 columns that can be selected from your customized work item table are available. This should cover fairly all information that you can imagine analysing and connecting from Team Foundation Server.\r\n<h2>Visual Studio Integration</h2>\r\nOn setup of TFS Timetracker Windows client, now also a plugin for Visual Studio is installed. This allows start tracking and check your pace directly from Visual Studio.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.tfs-timetracker.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/VSIntegrationBar.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1191\" src=\"http://blog.tfs-timetracker.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/VSIntegrationBar.png\" alt=\"VSIntegrationBar\" width=\"253\" height=\"27\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe new bar allows you to start tracking from any view of a workitem within Visual Studio.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.tfs-timetracker.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/VSIntegrationPanel.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1193\" src=\"http://blog.tfs-timetracker.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/VSIntegrationPanel.png\" alt=\"VSIntegrationPanel\" width=\"572\" height=\"199\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe new panel \"Time\" can be placed wherever you like within the Visual Studio interface. As soon an item is selected, is displays all available information from all linked sub items.\r\n<h2>Some more minor improvements and fixes</h2>\r\nHere is a list what has be done else in that release.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Added information about the parent of the item to the dialog for adding time (with support for full text search, just start typing, it will find parents as well as children that match your entry)</li>\r\n	<li>The field used to compute the velocity is now customizable (this is a \'per project\' setting)</li>\r\n	<li>In desktop client, the text of a non-TFS item is now kept after stopping the track</li>\r\n	<li>Fixed an issue that might caused to break the automatic reduction of estimated remaining work</li>\r\n	<li>Fixed an issue that might caused a null reference exception in the desktop client</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAnd, eh, yes, we changed the appearance a little - whereever you see an integration into Team Foundation Server, we no longer use \"Timetracker\", but just \"Time\".\r\n\r\nWe hope you enjoy our latest release and find some useful features for your daily work. Please continue giving us feedback, we appreciate to understand what is necessary for all your different environments and continue to deliver the best time recording for developers.', 'TFS Timetracker 2.6 released', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '1189-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-05-01 13:12:02', '2015-05-01 13:12:02', '', '1189', 'http://blog.tfs-timetracker.com/1189-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
