INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1264', '1', '2015-09-11 09:22:18', '2015-09-11 09:22:18', '<h1>Service release for TFS 2015</h1>\r\nWednesday evening we have released the 2.6.6 which fixes a bug that rarely affects some systems with Team Foundation Server 2015.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n<h2>Fixed issues</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Team Foundation Server 2015 only: In some cases TFS Timetracker Client for Windows was not able to connect to the server and connection errors occured.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPlease take our apologies that it was needed to adjust the release for Team Foundation Server 2015 one more time in such a short timeframe. There were quite a lot changes from Team Foundation Server RC1 to its final release (RTM), which made an unusual amount of adjustments necessary. While we are doing our best to test all possible scenarios that might happen, some gaps remain. The two last releases were necessary upon reports from users to our support. Thank you guys for reporting this and helping us to fix it that quickly!\r\n\r\nNo changes have been made to the releases for TFS 2012 and TFS 2013.\r\n\r\nThe download can be found here: <a href=\"http://www.tfs-timetracker.com/download\">http://www.tfs-timetracker.com/download</a>', 'TFS Timetracker 2.6.6', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'tfs-timetracker-2-6-6', '', '', '2015-10-01 19:19:23', '2015-10-01 19:19:23', '', '0', 'http://blog.tfs-timetracker.com/?p=1264', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('1265', '1', '2015-09-11 09:22:18', '2015-09-11 09:22:18', '<h1>Additional service release for Team Foundation Server 2015</h1>\r\nWednesday evening we have released the 2.6.6 which fixes a bug that rarely affects some systems with Team Foundation Server 2015.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nIn that case the TFS Timetracker Client for Windows was not able to connect to its server any longer, some connection errors occured.\r\n\r\nThe release of TFS Timetracker 2.6.6 resolves that issue.\r\n\r\nPlease take our apologies that we needed to adjust our release for Team Foundation Server 2015 now again in such a short timeframe. There were quite a lot changes from Team Foundation Server RC1 to its final release that made an unusual amount of adjustments necessary. While we are doing our best to test all possible scenarios that might happen, some gaps remain. The two last releases were necessary upon reports from users to our support. Thank you guys for reporting this and helping us to fix it that quickly!', 'TFS Timetracker 2.6.6', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1264-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-11 09:22:18', '2015-09-11 09:22:18', '', '1264', 'http://blog.tfs-timetracker.com/1264-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
